leads.lead_text: Plants velvety, appearing pale grey; leaves entire
Plants variously pubescent, not pale grey in colour; leaves distinctly 3–5-lobed
Calyx not prominently nerved, slender, the lobes longer than tube; petals pale pink; procumbent, short-lived perennial
Calyx lined by c. 20 longitudinal nerves, the lobes shorter than the inflated tube; petals yellow with a purple centre; annual to c. 60 cm high
